## Bug Report

<!-- Thanks for your bug report! Don't worry if you can't fill out all the sections. -->

### What version of TiKV are you using?
<!-- You can run `tikv-server --version` -->
master

### What operating system and CPU are you using?
<!-- If you're using Linux, you can run `cat /proc/cpuinfo` -->
x86_x64

### Steps to reproduce
<!-- If possible, provide a recipe for reproducing the error. A complete runnable program is good. -->
1. run `cargo run --package fuzz -- run Afl fuzz_codec_bytes`
2. see
```
12T08:58:49.336Z] error[E0599]: no method named `generate_files` found for type `&Builder` in the current scope
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z]   --> /rust/git/checkouts/protobuf-build-174b08b051947a10/42e52b9/src/lib.rs:56:14
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z]    |
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] 56 |         self.generate_files();
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z]    |              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ method not found in `&Builder`
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] 
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] error: aborting due to previous error
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] 
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0599`.
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] error: could not compile `protobuf-build`.
[2020-02-12T08:58:49.336Z] warning: build failed, waiting for other jobs to finish...
[2020-02-12T08:59:16.192Z] error: build failed
[2020-02-12T08:59:16.192Z] Running fuzzer failed: error building afl instrumented binary, exit code Some(101)
[2020-02-12T08:59:16.192Z] Error: 1
```

### What did you expect?
No error and start fuzz

### What did happened?
title: Can not run fuzzer
